This article is a transcript of a gaggle by Deputy Press Secretary Bill Burton aboard Air Force One. Burton discusses President Obama's upcoming town hall in Cleveland, Ohio, where he will talk about the economic pressure and anxiety faced by middle-class families. He also mentions the fights the administration has had to alleviate these issues, such as passing the Recovery Act. Burton mentions that the President will also address the problems with healthcare, including rising costs and lack of insurance. He emphasizes that the President is committed to fighting for these issues despite the challenges faced. The transcript also touches on other topics such as the confirmation process for Bernanke, the cyber security breach with China and the President's involvement in the State of the Union address. Burton also briefly mentions progress on bank regulations and makes a lighthearted remark about Jay Leno.